                </did>
                <scopecontent id="ref41">
                    <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
                    <p>This series contains materials relating to the life of Constance Parsons Hare. Most of the correspondence is from family members, particularly her sons and her sisters. Specific letters include a thank you letter from poet Edith Sitwell and two letters from Gertrude Parsons describing conditions in Germany and Paris after the end of World War I. Personal documents such as her will, a family tree, and a list of the monetary value of her property are also included.</p>
                </scopecontent>
